<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Bachelor's Locky Gilbert has confirmed he is still madly in love with the winner from the show. </p>

<p>The 31-year-old adventure seeker spoke to Perth Now on Sunday, while promoting the Western Australian indoor skydiving championships.  </p>

<p>Locky told the publication that 'the girl I'm in love with' could not attend the event. </p>

<p>Loved-up! The Bachelor's Locky Gilbert, 30, (pictured) has confirmed he is madly in love with the winner of the show to Perth Now, while competing in the indoor skydiving championships</p>

<p>The strapping Bachelor added his friends also could not attend.  </p>

<p>'My friends are used to me doing all kinds of stuff and they're like, ''We can't keep up with you'',' he added.</p>

<p>Locky admitted he had never done indoor skydiving before but he did some training before flying high.</p>

<p>Adventurous spirit! 'We did like an hour's worth of training this week and now we're in the championship,' Locky finished </p>

<p>'We did like an hour's worth of training this week and now we're in the championship,' he finished. </p>

<p>It comes amid news the girls of the Bachelor mansion will have to contend with a new blonde bombshell, Bec Cvilikas, on the show.    </p>

<p>In a teaser trailer for this week's episodes, host Osher Günsberg tells the remaining ladies another woman has entered the competition via video link.</p>

<p>Stunner: Bec Cvilikas will enter the Bachelor mansion, with the bombshell appearing on the show this week</p>

<p>'She's frickin amazing!' an excited Locky gushes in a piece-to-camera. 'All the boxes are being ticked.' </p>

<p>But while Bachelor Locky is thrilled about the new arrival, fellow suitor Izzy Sharman-Firth describes the newcomer as a 'kick in the d**k'.   </p>

<p>Last month, Daily Mail Australia published images of Bec at a rose ceremony following hometown week, which was filmed in July.</p>

<p>Will she be The One? Bella (L) and Irena's place in the top five isn't surprising, as they've both been tipped as favourites for weeks. Right: Locky Gilbert</p>

<p>Five women were pictured on the grounds of the estate: Irena Srbinovska, Kaitlyn Hoppe, Bella Varelis, Izzy Sharman-Firth and Bec. </p>

<p>Bella and Irena's place in the top five isn't surprising, as they've both been tipped as favourites since the season premiere. </p>

<p>The Bachelor continues Wednesday at 7.30pm on Channel 10</p>

<p>Who will win his heart? The Bachelor continues Wednesday at 7.30pm on Channel 10</p>
